get_commits(before, number)[source]¶

Retrieves and array of the latest (sorted by timestamp) commits for the project. If timestamp is given it will get <b>number</b> of commits strictly before <b>before</b>. If commit hash is specified that commit will be included too. <br> N.B. due to slight time differences on different machines, ancestors may be returned before their descendants. Unless looking for ‘headless’ commits ‘getHistory’ is the preferred method.

Parameters

  • before (int or float or str) – Timestamp or commitHash to load history from.

  • number (int or float) – Number of commits to load.

Returns

The commits that match the input, ordered by their time of insertion.

Return type

list of dict

Raises

JSError – The result of the execution.

get_common_ancestor_commit(commit_a, commit_b)[source]¶

Retrieves the common ancestor of two commits. If no ancestor exists it will result in an error.

Parameters

  • commit_b (str) – Commit hash.

Returns

The commit hash of the common ancestor.

Return type

str

Raises

JSError – The result of the execution (will be non-null if e.g. the commits do not exist or have no common ancestor).

get_history(start, number)[source]¶

Retrieves an array of commits starting from a branch(es) and/or commitHash(es). <br> The result is ordered by the rules (applied in order) <br> 1. Descendants are always returned before their ancestors. <br> 2. By their timestamp.

Parameters

  • start (str or str or list of str or list of str) – Branch name, commit hash or array of these.

  • number (int or float) – Number of commits to load.

Returns

The commits that match the input ordered as explained.

Return type

list of dict

Raises

JSError – The result of the execution.

make_commit(branch_name, parents, root_hash, core_objects, msg)[source]¶

Makes a commit to data base. Based on the root hash and commit message a new {@link module:Storage.CommitObject} (with returned hash) is generated and insert together with the core objects to the database on the server.

Parameters

  • branch_name (str) – Name of branch to update (none if null).

  • parents (list of str) – Parent commit hashes.

  • root_hash (str) – Hash of root object.

  • core_objects (dict) – Core objects associated with the commit.

  • msg (str) – Commit message.

Returns

Status about the commit and branch update.

Return type

dict

Raises

JSError – The result of the execution.
